      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JESSE RAIDER (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner (17.52). Has winning claims on his best figures. RADIO RAMSGATE (6) has a strong record this trip with two wins and two placings from five starts. Recorded a 2 length win (17.29) in a Novice race last time at this track. Looks suited here and can measure up. SCELZI (7) doesn't win out of turn. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when second (17.43) at this track. Goes very well at the trip finding the frame in each of four starts. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Will give a great sight again. FELON DAVE (2) has claims fresh from a recent placing at big odds.",
